The little horned toad (Megophrys minor), also known as the dwarf horned toad, Kwangshien spadefoot toad, or tiny spadefoot toad,  is a species of frog in the family Megophryidae. It is found in southern China, Thailand, Vietnam, and possibly in Laos and Myanmar. It has recently been reported from Bhutan.
Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests, subtropical or tropical moist montane forests, rivers, and swamps. It is threatened by habitat loss.